webpackJsonp([0xc25cb0b082dc],{783:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{wordpressPost:{title:"Wider open access developments at the BMJ Group",content:'<p>By adopting an open access policy for research articles, <em>BMJ Open</em> follows in the footsteps of the <em>BMJ</em> itself. All research articles published in the <em>BMJ</em> are available open access, a policy that dates from 1998. A <a href="http://www.bmj.com/cgi/content/extract/341/aug17_3/c4494" target="_blank">recent editorial</a> in the <em>BMJ</em> talks about the launch of <em>BMJ Open</em> and the <em>BMJ</em>&#8216;s new policy on open access charges.</p>\n<p>One of the editorial&#8217;s authors, and <em>BMJ </em>deputy editor, Dr Trish Groves has also opened the issue up for discussion on doc2doc <a href="http://doc2doc.bmj.com/forums.html?slGroupKey=32da9f1b-d97b-4c32-8ca2-bd6305018693&amp;slPage=showDiscussionPost&amp;slForumPostKey=Cat%3aprivateForum%3aecd06e13-7891-4bae-a896-a0fb39a3af0c%40D%7c9%3b36%7cCommGroup32da9f1b-d97b-4c32-8ca2-bd6305018693%7cDiscussion%3a2a8c154f-6d7f-444e-9817-ad6a2aa77508&amp;plckFindPostKey=Cat:privateForum:ecd06e13-7891-4bae-a896-a0fb39a3af0c@D|9;36|CommGroup32da9f1b-d97b-4c32-8ca2-bd6305018693|Discussion:2a8c154f-6d7f-444e-9817-ad6a2aa77508Post:13e564c3-efe5-48c9-80a9-c540a64419be" target="_blank">here</a>.<!--TrendMD v2.4.3--></p>\n'},site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Gatsby Default Starter"}}},pathContext:{id:"7b3bcf81-31b7-5de8-8800-29e2387d2007"}}}});
